Bathing Beauty
This amazing looking fellow was quietly sitting in the water at Tenryu-ji temple at Arashi-yama in Kyoto. All of those bits floating around him and on top of him are sakura petals. Any help with identifying the species would be greatly appreciated.

Apparently this little fella is an <a href="http://www.rieo.net/amph/frog/usi.htm">American Bullfrog</a> <i>Rana (Aquarana) catesbeian</i>. A big thank you to <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/wolfnowl/">wolfnowl</a> for the ID.

